peaceful /ˈpiːsfʊl/

1. ADJ Peaceful activities and situations do not involve war. 和平的 (活动、局面) 

例： He has attempted to find a peaceful solution to the Ossetian conflict. 他曾试图找到一个解决奥塞梯冲突的和平的办法。 

2. peacefully ADV 和平地 [ADV with v] 

例： The U.S. military expects the matter to be resolved peacefully. 美国军方期望这一事件能和平解决。 

3. ADJ Peaceful occasions happen without violence or serious disorder. 和平的 (场景) 

例： The farmers staged a noisy but peaceful protest outside the headquarters of the organization. 农民们在该组织总部外举行了一次喧闹但和平的抗议活动。 

4. peacefully ADV 和平地 [ADV with v] 

例： The governor asked the crowd of protestors to leave peacefully. 州长要求抗议人群和平离开。 

5. ADJ Peaceful people are not violent and try to avoid arguing or fighting with other people. 和平的 (人们) 

例： ...warriors who killed or enslaved the peaceful farmers. …杀死或奴役和平的农民们的那些武士。 

6. peacefully ADV 和平地 [ADV with v] 

例： They've been living and working peacefully with members of various ethnic groups. 他们一直与各种族群的成员们和平地生活和工作。 

7. ADJ A peaceful place or time is quiet, calm, and free from disturbance. 安宁的 (地方、时期) 

例： ...a peaceful house in the heart of the Ozarks. …在欧扎克山脉中心地带的一幢安宁的房子。 

8. peacefully ADV 安宁地 [ADV after v] 

例： Except for traffic noise the night passed peacefully. 除了交通噪音，那夜安宁地过去了。

